latestPosts.caption:
Everything I had at the Traditional Buffet at @colombokitchen_ldn — all under 1 min 🇱🇰🍴
(Everything is shown in the order it appears in the reel 👇🏽)

1️⃣ Fragrant Yellow Rice & Red Rice – two types of perfectly cooked Sri Lankan rice, one buttery and vibrant, the other earthy and wholesome

2️⃣ Fish Ambul Thiyal – a bold, blackened sour fish curry, rich in spices and full of depth

3️⃣ Negombo Chicken Curry – tender chicken slow-cooked in a rich, spiced coconut gravy — full of homestyle flavour

4️⃣ Parippu (Dhal/Lentil Curry) – creamy, comforting, and a must with every Sri Lankan meal

5️⃣ Manioc – boiled cassava, simple yet filling, very flavorful!

6️⃣ Jackfruit Curry – a hearty, meaty vegan curry with deep, slow-cooked spices

7️⃣ Aubergine Moju – sweet, sticky, and tangy fried aubergine — one of my faves!

8️⃣ Gotukola Sambal – fresh green sambal made with finely shredded gotukola, coconut & lime

9️⃣ Papadam – crispy, golden perfection (always take extras haha)

🍹Drinks included the Colombo Sunrise (tropical and sweet — summer in a glass!) and the Lime & Mint Cooler (fresh, fizzy, and alcohol-free).

📍The Traditional Buffet runs on every last Sunday of the month from 12PM onwards — check @colombokitchen_ldn ’s page for the latest updates.

More on the vibe, food & full experience is saved on my IG Highlights — go have a peek! 👀✨
.

latestPosts.caption:
Drinks @colombokitchen_ldn 🍹
Here’s what we had ⬇️

✨ Colombo Sunrise — coconut and pineapple juice topped with cranberry.
Tastes exactly like summer in a glass — sweet, tropical, and just the right amount of tang. Definitely my new fave 🌅

🌿 Lime & Mint Cooler — fresh lime juice, mint leaves and elderflower syrup, topped with soda water.
Light, refreshing and perfect for when you’re not drinking but still want something fun.

Mocktails + good food = always a good idea 💛
.
